<div class="row g-4"><div class="col-12"><div class="Wrapper_wrapper__raXe4 Card_card__7rJy4 bg-body-secondary rounded-3 p-4 card position-relative ContentBlock_content__MOc3W" data-type="specPoint"><h2 id="introduction-to-climate-change">Introduction to Climate Change</h2><ul><li><p>The termÂ <b>climate</b> refers to the <b>weather conditions</b> in a region over a <b>long period of time</b> i.e. several decades</p></li><li><p>When the weather conditions in a region change significantly over a long period of time, this is <b>climate change</b></p></li><li><p>Changes to the climate have <b>occurred frequently throughout Earth's history</b> due to changes in factors such as atmospheric gas concentrations and volcanic activity, but climate changes that have occurred <b>since the mid-1800s</b> are thought to be the result of <b>human activities</b></p><ul><li><p>The term climate change is most often used today to refer to <b>global warming</b> that is occurring as a result of human activities</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Changes to <b>global climate patterns</b> result in alterations to <b>local weather patterns</b> e.g. rainfall and temperatures</p></li></ul><div class="mb-5" data-type="image"><img alt="Climate Change - Graph Temperature Evolution" class="ContentBlock_figure__6whpf" data-nimg="1" decoding="async" height="899" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 320w, (max-width: 640px) 640w, (max-width: 960px) 960w, (max-width: 1280px) 1280w, 1920w" src="Climate-Change-Graph-Temperature-Evolution.png" srcset="https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=16/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/02/Climate-Change-Graph-Temperature-Evolution.png 16w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=32/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/02/Climate-Change-Graph-Temperature-Evolution.png 32w, https://cdn.savemyexams.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,width=48/https://cdn.savemyexams.com/uploads/2020/02/Climate-Change-Graph-Temperature-Evolution.png 48w, https://cdn.savemye